February 22, 2022, 08:31
24,400 cases of covid were recorded in Ukraine per day, 33,200 Ukrainians recovered
On February 21, 56,700 people were vaccinated, half of them with the second dose.
Vera Kasiyan
, news editor
Facebook
Twitter
LB.ua in Google News
Photo: EPA/UPG
On Monday, February 21, 24,440 cases were recorded in Ukraine
coronavirus disease COVID-19
. In particular, the disease was diagnosed in 2,455 children and 665 medical workers.
According to the data
press service of the Ministry of Health
, with confirmed and suspected cases, 1,553 patients were hospitalized yesterday. 33,238 people recovered, 287 people died.
The number of diseases in the regions per day:
Kyiv - 2,297;
Vinnytsia region – 140;
Volyn region - 443;
Dnipropetrovsk region - 1,353;
Donetsk region – 593;
Zhytomyr Region – 480;
