Ternopil region - 156;
Kharkiv region - 911;
Kherson region – 582;
Khmelnytskyi region – 203;
Cherkasy region – 633;
Chernivtsi region – 184;
Chernihiv region - 368.
There are no data from the temporarily occupied territories of the Republic of Crimea, Donetsk, Luhansk regions and the city of Sevastopol.
During the entire period of the pandemic in Ukraine, 4,758,773 people fell ill, 3,985,601 people recovered from the coronavirus, and 104,932 Ukrainians died from complications of covid.
According to the Ministry of Health, last day
vaccinated against COVID-19
56,726 Ukrainians. 15,443 people received the first dose, 26,027 received the second dose. 350 people were additionally vaccinated, 14,906 were vaccinated with a "booster".
Since the beginning of the vaccination campaign in Ukraine, 15,695,806 people have been vaccinated. 15,695,804 received one dose, 15,148,026 received two doses. 26,860 people were additionally vaccinated, 683,414 people were given a booster dose.
A total of 31,554,104 covid vaccinations were administered.
We will remind you that the incidence of covid in Ukraine has been decreasing for more than three weeks in a row. According to the head of the Ministry of Health Viktor Lyashko,
the peak of the incidence of coronavirus in Ukraine will pass in 2-3 weeks.
Vera Kasiyan
, news editor
